    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">A</span> Strike</p><hr /><p>An earth bomb contains sticky clay with sharpened pebbles, all magically enhanced to hamper movement and dig into the skin. An adamantoise fragment deals 2d6 earth damage, 2 earth splash damage, and requires an [[/act escape dc=19]]{Escape Check}. You gain a +1 item bonus to attack rolls.</p><p>On a critical hit, a creature in contact with a solid surface becomes stuck to the surface and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.eIcWbB5o3pP6OIMe]{Immobilized} for 1 round, and a creature flying via wings has its wings tangled, causing it to fall safely to the ground and become unable to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.cS9nfDRGD83bNU1p]{Fly} again for 1 round. This effect does not function when used on a creature that is in water.</p><p>The target can end any effects by using the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.SkZAQRkLLkmBQNB9]{Escape} action or spending a total of 3 @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.pvQ5rY2zrtPI614F]{Interact} actions to carefully remove the sticky substances. These Interact actions donâ€™t have to be consecutive, and other creatures can provide the actions as well.</p>"
